    "body": "## Summary\n\nThis change teaches the CUDA code generator to fuse packed x2 `mul + add` patterns into `tl::fma2` when the operands already qualify for packed x2 emission.\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Added a shared `CanEmitPackedX2Math` helper for packed x2 math eligibility in CUDA codegen.\n- Extended the packed x2 vector binary fast path to detect `Add(Mul(a, b), c)` and `Add(c, Mul(a, b))`, then emit `tl::fma2` directly instead of separate `tl::mul2` and `tl::add2` calls.\n- Added the same fusion for explicit packed-call forms such as `tl::add2(tl::mul2(...), c)` in the call emission path.\n- Added CUDA codegen tests that verify auto-vectorized `mul + add` emits `tl::fma2` for:\n  - `float32` on `sm_100`\n  - `bfloat16` on `sm_80`\n  - `float16` on `sm_80`\n\n## Why\n\nThe existing CUDA vector codegen already lowered packed x2 multiplication and addition separately, but it did not fuse the common multiply-accumulate pattern into `fma2`. That left an avoidable intermediate packed value in the generated source and missed the dedicated packed FMA helper that already exists in the CUDA templates.\n\n## Impact\n\n- Auto-vectorized CUDA kernels now generate tighter packed x2 source for eligible multiply-accumulate expressions.\n- Existing packed x2 codegen coverage remains intact.\n- The change is limited to the CUDA packed x2 fast path and does not affect unsupported dtypes or lane configurations.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `./format.sh`\n  - `pre-commit` passed\n  - `clang-tidy` failed in the local environment because Clang could not find `stddef.h`\n- `PYTHONPATH=/nfs-df/prod/data/permanent/wanglei/tilelang_ref:/nfs-df/prod/data/permanent/wanglei/tilelang_ref/3rdparty/tvm/python:/nfs-df/prod/data/permanent/wanglei/tilelang_ref/build/tvm:/nfs-df/prod/data/permanent/wanglei/tilelang_ref/build/lib PYTEST_DISABLE_PLUGIN_AUTOLOAD=1 python -m pytest -q testing/python/cuda/test_cuda_f32x2_intrinsics.py -k 'codegen'`\n  - Passed: `39 passed, 21 deselected`\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n## Release Notes\n\n* **Improvements**\n  * Enhanced CUDA code generation for mathematical vector operations, with optimized support for fused multiply-add patterns on float32, bfloat16, and float16 types on compatible GPU architectures (SM80, SM100+).\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added new test coverage for CUDA vector operation code generation optimization.\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
